1. c4 e5 2. Nc3 Nc6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. e3 d5 5. cxd5 Nxd5 6. Bb5 Nxc3 7. bxc3 Bd6 8. d4 Bd7 9. e4 exd4 10. cxd4 Bb4+ 11. Bd2 Bxd2+ 12. Qxd2 O-O 13. O-O Qe7 14. Qf4 Ne5 15. Be2 Nxf3+ 16. Bxf3 Rac8 17. d5 Rfe8 18. Rfe1 Qd6 19. Qe3 b6 20. Red1 Re7 21. Rac1 Rce8 22. Qc3 Bc8 23. Qc6 $2 Qxc6 24. Rxc6 $5 (24. dxc6 f6 {gives a positional disadvantage for White.}) 24... f5 $1 25. e5 ({White also loses a pawn by} 25. Rdc1 fxe4 26. Bh5 g6 27. Be2 Bb7 28. Rxc7 Bxd5) 25... Bb7 26. Rc3 Rxe5 27. h4 Re1+ 28. Rxe1 Rxe1+ 29. Kh2 Re7 30. Kg3 Kf7 31. Kf4 Kf6 32. g4 $2 {Nimzowitsch further ruins his position.} fxg4 33. Kxg4 Rd7 34. Kf4 Bxd5 35. Bxd5 Rxd5 36. Rc6+ Rd6 37. Rxc7 Rd4+ 38. Kg3 Ra4 39. Rc2 h5 40. f3 g5 41. hxg5+ Kxg5 42. Rg2 Ra3 43. Re2 h4+ 44. Kg2 Ra4 45. Rc2 Kf4 46. Rb2 h3+ 47. Kxh3 Kxf3 {Black plays a fine rook ending.} 48. Rh2 Ke3 49. Kg3 Kd3 50. Kf3 Kc3 51. Ke3 Rb4 52. Rh7 a5 53. Rh2 b5 54. Rd2 a4 55. Rf2 Rb2 56. Rf5 Kb4 57. Kd3 Rxa2 58. Rf4+ Kb3 59. Rf3 Rh2 60. Kd4+ Kb2 61. Rf5 b4 62. Kc4 a3 63. Kxb4 a2 64. Rf2+ Rxf2 {Spielmann had achieved the same number of points as the leader Capablanca, but he had played one more game.} 0-1


