{[%evp 0,69,30,36,14,25,13,8,10,7,21,5,7,-1,6,0,12,29,29,18,18,-10,-5,-31,-28,-32,-11,2,50,6,49,0,80,29,38,38,54,35,28,26,61,72,126,117,136,115,202,149,192,207,220,199,366,380,377,423,423,443,553,553,553,510,595,378,405,414,463,453,712,712,780,808]} {Sources: 1. Muenchener Zeitung, 17 June 1905. 2) Per Skjoldager,Jorn Erik Nielsen: Aron Nimzowitsch: On The Road To Chess Mastery, 1886-1924.} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 Bb4 6. Nxc6 bxc6 7. Bd3 d5 8. exd5 cxd5 9. O-O O-O 10. Bg5 {This line was already well known at the time the game was played.} c6 11. Ne2 h6 ({In the same match, Nimzowitsch as Black, opted for} 11... Bd6 12. Nd4 Bd7 {with an even play 1-0 (42) Spielmann,R-Nimzowitsch,A Munich 1905}) 12. Bh4 g5 ({Most often played is} 12... Bd6) ({In the same year, Nimzowitsch faced with} 12... Re8 13. Nd4 Bd7 14. Qf3 c5 15. Nf5 Bxf5 16. Bxf5 g5 $13 {½-½ (42) Nimzowitsch,A-Reggio,A Barmen 1905 The game move leads to a sharp position.}) 13. Bg3 ({Preferable was} 13. c3 $5 Bc5 14. Bg3 Bg4) 13... Ne4 ({Natural idea. Probably best was} 13... Re8 $11) 14. c3 ({Interesting was} 14. Nd4 $14) 14... Bc5 15. Qa4 Qe8 $6 ({Suspicious move. More natural was} 15... Nxg3 16. Nxg3 Bd7 $11) 16. Rfe1 (16. Nd4 $14) 16... f5 $1 $11 {After this double edged move the position is even.} 17. Nd4 Bxd4 $2 (17... f4 $2 18. Bxe4 dxe4 19. Qc4+ $18 {Nimzowitsch}) ({This exchange is a decisive mistake. After} 17... Bb6 {the position is even.}) 18. Qxd4 ({At the time this game was played, Nimzowitsch was not so strong strategicall player. Stronger was} 18. cxd4) 18... Qf7 19. f3 Nxg3 $2 ({Stronger is} 19... c5 20. Qa4 Nxg3 21. hxg3 Rb8 22. Rad1 Rxb2 23. Qa3 Qb7 24. Bf1 $16) 20. hxg3 Be6 $2 ({This move definitely loses the game. Better was} 20... a5 21. Qe5 Rd8 22. Rad1 Qg7 23. Bxf5 Qxe5 24. Rxe5 Bxf5 25. Rxf5 Rd6 {Black has good chances for salvation.}) 21. Re5 $18 {[%csl Yc5,Ye5,Yf6,Yg7] White dominates on dark squares.} Rfe8 22. Rae1 Qd7 ({In the case of} 22... Bd7 23. Rxe8+ Bxe8 24. a4 $18 {From strategical point of view, Black is lost.}) 23. Kf2 Qf7 24. Qc5 Qd7 25. f4 ({Easier was} 25. Rxe6 Rxe6 26. Bxf5 Rae8 27. Rxe6 Rxe6 28. Bxe6+ Qxe6 29. Qxa7 $18) 25... Kg7 26. Bxf5 ({Good alternative was} 26. fxg5 hxg5 27. g4 $18) 26... Bxf5 27. Re7+ Rxe7 28. Rxe7+ Kf6 29. Rxd7 Bxd7 30. Qd6+ Be6 31. Qxc6 Rb8 32. b4 Rc8 33. Qd6 Rc4 34. Qe5+ Kf7 35. f5 1-0


