{Prié, Eric: 'ChessCalisthenics: 'B13: Caro-Kann: Exchange Variation and Panov-Botvinnik Attack''} {Prié, Eric: 'Petronijevic,Zoran: 'In his comments of this game great chess master Nimzowitsch calls readers' attention to the problem of the centre: mistakes in the centre are inadmissible.'' Prié, Eric: 'Petronijevic,Zoran: 'In seinem Kommentar zu dieser Partie lenkt der große Schachmeister Nimzowitsch die Aufmerksamkeit der Leser auf das Zemtrum: Fehler im Zentrum dürfen unter keinen Umständen gemacht werden. ''} 1. e4 {Prié, Eric Prié, Eric: 'Petronijevic,Zoran'} c6 2. d4 d5 3. exd5 cxd5 (3... Qxd5 4. Nc3 Qd8 (4... Qa5)) 4. c3 ({Prié, Eric: 'Nowadays the move' Prié, Eric: 'Heutzutage wird der Zug'} 4. Bd3 {Prié, Eric: 'Petronijevic,Zoran' Prié, Eric: 'is considered to be most precise because it prevents Black from developing his c8 on the natural f5 square. The bishop on d3 is useful for keeping the e4-square and if Black castles on the short side it will exert pressure on the h7-square.' Prié, Eric: 'als genauste Fortsetzung empfohlen, weil er Schwarz daran hindert, seinen c8 auf das natürliche Feld f5 zu entwickeln. Der Läufer steht auf d3 gut, um das Feld e4 zu kontrollieren und wenn Schwarz kurz rochiert, zielt er stark gegen das Feld h7. '}) (4. Nf3) (4. c4 Nf6 5. Nf3 (5. Nc3 {Mieses-Schlechter, Breslau 1912} Nc6 6. cxd5 Nxd5 7. Bc4 Be6 $1) 5... Nc6 (5... g6 {Leonhardt-Fahrni, 1905} 6. Nc3 Bg7 7. Bg5 Ne4 8. cxd5 Nxg5 9. Nxg5 Qb6 (9... e5 $1)) 6. Nc3 e6 7. c5 Ne4 8. Qc2 {Reti-Duras, Wien (Vienna) 1908.}) 4... Nc6 ({Prié, Eric: 'A flexible move which offers Black more possibilities for future development. Also played is' Prié, Eric: 'Eine flexible Fortsetzung, die Schwarz verschiedene Möglichkeiten für die spätere Entwicklung offen lässt. Gespielt wird auch'} 4... Nf6 {Prié, Eric: 'Petronijevic,Zoran'}) ({Inferior is Schlechter ist} 4... Bf5 {(Prié, Eric) Petronijevic,Zoran} 5. Qb3 $14 {[%cal Rb3b7]}) 5. Bf4 {5...e5 Prié, Eric: '?!' '?!'} ({Prié, Eric: 'With the move' Prié, Eric: 'Mit dem Zug'} 5. Bd3 {Prié, Eric: 'Petronijevic,Zoran' Prié, Eric: 'White transposes to the main variation of The Exchange Variation.' Prié, Eric: 'leitet Weiß zur Hauptvariante der Abtauschvariante über.'}) 5... Bf5 $1 {Prié, Eric: 'Petronijevic,Zoran: 'In such kind of positions the exchange of the light-squared bishops suits Black since his d5 is on a light square and the white c3 and d4 are on dark squares. With the game move Black controls the b1-h7 diagonal.'' Prié, Eric: 'Petronijevic,Zoran: 'In diesen Stellungstypen passt Schwarz der Tasch der weißfeldrigen Läufer, weil der d5 auf einem weißen Feld steht und die weißen c3 und d4 stehen auf schwarzen Feldern. Mit dem Partiezug kontrolliert Schwarz die Diagonale b1-h7l.''} (5... Nf6 6. Bd3 $1 (6. Nd2 {Spielmann-Tartakower, Copenhagen 1923} g6 7. Ngf3 Bg7 8. h3 Ne4 $1) 6... e6 7. Nf3) 6. Nf3 (6. Bd3 Bxd3 {Prié, Eric} 7. Qxd3 e6 (7... Nf6 $11 {[%csl Yc4] Petronijevic,Zoran}) 8. Nf3 Bd6 9. Bxd6 Qxd6 10. O-O Nge7 11. Nbd2 h6 12. a4 O-O 13. a5 Ng6 14. Rfe1 Rfe8 15. g3 e5 16. dxe5 Ngxe5 17. Nxe5 Nxe5 18. Qd4 Nc6 19. Qa4 d4 20. cxd4 Qxd4 {Sermek,D (2530)-Mikhalchishin,A (2538)/Murska Sobota 2006/EXT 2008/1/2-1/2}) 6... e6 {Prié, Eric: 'Apparently this typical structure (here reversed whereas generally issued from 1.d4 d5 2. c4 e6 followed by White exchanging on d5) was scrutinized in the tournament to such an extent that it gave its name to it: The Karlsbad (or Carlsbad) structure!'} 7. Qb3 Qd7 (7... Qc8 {Prié, Eric} 8. Nbd2 Be7 9. h3 Nf6 10. Nh4 Be4 11. Nxe4 dxe4 12. g3 Nd5 13. Ng2 Nxf4 14. Nxf4 Bd6 15. d5 exd5 16. Nxd5 O-O 17. Bg2 Re8 18. O-O Ne5 19. Rae1 Nf3+ 20. Bxf3 exf3 21. Rxe8+ Qxe8 22. Qxb7 {Sulskis,S (2577) -Asrian,K (2591)/Batumi 2002/CBM 090/1/2-1/2 (35)}) 8. Nbd2 (8. Ne5 Qc8 9. Nd2 f6 $1 10. Nxc6 bxc6) 8... f6 $1 {Prié, Eric: 'Even here, with the London diagonal open, this idea poses White problems, for in return the opposing d5 pawn is protected against any further c3-c4 as in the previous game. Petronijevic,Zoran: '!?'' Prié, Eric: 'Petronijevic,Zoran: 'According to Nimzowitsch Black has a compensation for his weak e6 in the form of the well placed bishop on f5.  '' Prié, Eric: 'Petronijevic,Zoran: 'Nach Nimzowitsch hat Schwarz Kompensation für seinen schwachen e6, weil der Läufer auf f5 sehr gut steht. ''} (8... Nge7 9. Be2) 9. Be2 ({Prié, Eric: 'A passive move.' Prié, Eric: 'Ein passiver Zug.'} 9. c4 {Prié, Eric: '' Prié, Eric: 'Petronijevic,Zoran' Prié, Eric: 'because in such kind of positions it is neccessary to attack the centre.' Prié, Eric: ', weil es in diesen Stellungstypen wichtig ist, das Zemtrum anzugreifen.'}) (9. h4 Nh6 $1 {Prié, Eric} 10. Bxh6 (10. Be2 Ng4 11. Nf1 e5) 10... gxh6 11. Be2 O-O-O) (9. h3 {Prié, Eric} g5 10. Bh2 h5 {Does not help White.}) 9... g5 (9... Nge7 {Prié, Eric} 10. O-O g5 11. Bg3 (11. Be3 Bg7 12. Rac1 O-O 13. c4 Bg6 14. Qa4 Rfd8 15. cxd5 Nxd5 16. Nb3 Qe7 17. Bd2 Nb6 18. Qb5 Rd5 19. Rc5 g4 20. Rxd5 gxf3 21. Rc5 fxe2 22. Rfc1 Rd8 23. Qxe2 {Seul,G (2460)-Lalic,B (2515)/Germany 2004/EXT 2006/0-1 (39)}) 11... h5 12. h4 g4 13. Ne1 Bh6 14. Rd1 Bg6 15. Nd3 Bxd3 $1 16. Bxd3 f5 17. Be5 Nxe5 18. dxe5 O-O $2 (18... O-O-O 19. c4 Kb8 20. cxd5 Nxd5 21. Bc4 Nf4 $1 22. g3 Nh3+ 23. Kg2 Bxd2) 19. c4 d4 20. c5 Nd5 21. Nc4 $132 {Schmidt Schaeffer, S (2310)-Vonthron, H (2335) Germany 2004}) 10. Bg3 (10. Be3 {(Prié, Eric) Petronijevic,Zoran: '!?'} Bd6) 10... h5 11. h3 (11. h4 $5 $13 {(Prié, Eric) Petronijevic,Zoran Petronijevic Petronijevic}) 11... Nge7 (11... Rc8 {Prié, Eric} 12. O-O Nge7 13. Qd1 Ng6 14. Ne1 h4 15. Bh2 Bd6 {Wohl, A (2388)-Laketic, G  (2446) Lido Estensi 2002 1/2(51)} 16. Bxd6 Qxd6 17. Bd3 Bxd3 18. Nxd3 $13) 12. O-O {Prié, Eric: '?' '?' Prié, Eric: 'Castling 'coffin side''} (12. Qd1 {next Nb3 and Bd3}) (12. Nf1 {Prié, Eric} Bg6 (12... Be4 $15) 13. Ne3 Nf5 14. Nxf5 Bxf5 15. a4 $13) ({White castles on the short side which is a mistake because Black has prepared to launch an attack on the kingside. Es ist ein Fehler, dass Weiß kurz rochiert, denn Schwarz bereitet gerade einen Angriff am Königsflügel vor.} 12. c4 $142 {(Prié, Eric) Petronijevic,Zoran} dxc4 13. Bxc4 Nd5 {[%csl Yd5] although now Black has an excellent position. obwohl Schwarz nun eine starke Stellung hat.}) 12... Bh6 13. Ne1 {Prié, Eric: '?' '?'} (13. Qd1 $142 {(Prié, Eric) ChessCalisthenics: '=!?'} Ng6 (13... Bg6 14. Ne1 Nf5 $2 15. Bxh5) 14. Ne1 $140 g4 $1 15. hxg4 hxg4 16. Bxg4 e5 $44 17. Bxf5 Qxf5 18. Nc2 Nf4 $1 $40 19. Ne3 $2 Qh7) 13... g4 14. Qd1 Bxd2 15. Qxd2 gxh3 {Prié, Eric: '' '' Prié, Eric: 'Black is a pawn up with an attack. No "overprotection" or "blockade", the most famous chess theoretician ever now finishes in style, somewhat helped, it has to be said, by the opponent's lack of defensive stubbornness. Petronijevic,Zoran: '-+''} 16. Nd3 b6 (16... h4 $1 {Prié, Eric} 17. Nc5 Qc8 18. Bd6 hxg2 19. Kxg2 b6 20. Ba6 Qd8 21. Nb7 Qd7 $19) (16... Bxd3 $5 {(Prié, Eric) Petronijevic,Zoran} 17. Qxd3 (17. Bxd3 h4 18. Bh2 hxg2) 17... h4 18. Bh2 hxg2 $19) 17. Rfe1 (17. Nf4 {(Prié, Eric) ChessCalisthenics: '!?'} h4 $1 18. Bh5+ Kd8 (18... Rxh5 $4 19. Nxh5 {And f6 hangs.}) 19. Bxh4 hxg2 20. Rfe1 (20. Kxg2 e5) 20... Kc7 21. Bxf6 Rh7 $17) 17... h4 18. Bh2 Kf7 $1 {Prié, Eric: 'Petronijevic,Zoran: '!'' Prié, Eric: 'Petronijevic,Zoran: 'Black removes his king in order to bring his a8 into play by g8.'' Prié, Eric: 'Petronijevic,Zoran: 'Schwarz zieht seinen König zur Seite, um seinen a8 mit g8 in den Angriff einzuschalten.''} (18... hxg2 {Prié, Eric} 19. Nf4 h3 20. Bh5+ Kf8 21. Qe2 e5 $19) (18... O-O-O $4 {(Prié, Eric) Petronijevic,Zoran is bad because of ist fehlerhaft, wegen} 19. Nc5 $18 {[%cal Yh2b8,Re2a6]}) 19. g4 {Prié, Eric: '?!' '?!' Prié, Eric: 'Petronijevic,Zoran: 'A desperate try.'' Prié, Eric: 'Petronijevic,Zoran: 'ein Desperadozug.''} (19. gxh3 $142 {Prié, Eric} Bxh3 (19... Rag8+ 20. Bg4 Bxd3 21. Qxd3 $17) 20. Kh1 $17) 19... hxg3 20. Bxg3 (20. fxg3 {Prié, Eric} Rag8 $17) 20... h2+ 21. Kg2 {Prié, Eric: '?' '?'} ({Petronijevic,Zoran: 'Better was' Petronijevic,Zoran: 'Besser war'} 21. Kh1 {Prié, Eric Petronijevic,Zoran: 'although White has no moves good enough to save the game.' Petronijevic,Zoran: ', obwohl Weiß keine Züge mehr zur Verfügung hat, um das Spiel noch zu retten.'} Be4+ (21... Rag8 22. Bf3 Bxd3 23. Qxd3 Nf5 $17) (21... Ng6 {Petronijevic,Zoran}) 22. f3 Rag8) 21... Be4+ ({Petronijevic,Zoran: 'Better was' Petronijevic,Zoran: 'Besser war'} 21... e5 {(Prié, Eric) Petronijevic,Zoran: '!'} 22. dxe5 Be4+ 23. f3 Qh3+ ({stronger than Nimzowitsch's move stärker als der Zug von Nimzowitsch} 23... Rag8 {Petronijevic,Zoran} 24. Nf2 $1 ({The move Der Zug} 24. e6+ {was recommended by Nimzowitsch but it is bad because of wurde von Nimzowitsch empfohlen, aber er ist schlecht, wegen} Qxe6 25. Nf4 Qg4 $19) 24... Nf5 $17) 24. Kf2 (24. Kh1 Qxg3 (24... Nf5 {Petronijevic,Zoran} 25. e6+ Ke8 $19) 25. fxe4 Rag8 26. exd5 Qg1+) 24... Rag8 {Petronijevic,Zoran: '-+'} 25. Bf4 Qg2+ 26. Ke3 Nf5#) 22. Bf3 {Prié, Eric: 'Petronijevic,Zoran: '?''} (22. f3 {Prié, Eric: 'Petronijevic,Zoran: '''} Bxd3 (22... Nf5 23. fxe4 dxe4 24. Nf4) (22... e5 23. Nf2) (22... Rag8) 23. Bxd3 Rag8 (23... e5 {(Prié, Eric) ChessCalisthenics: ''} 24. Kh1 Qh3 25. Qf2 Rag8 26. Bxh2 exd4 $19 27. cxd4 $140 Nxd4 $1)) 22... Nf5 (22... e5 {(Prié, Eric) Petronijevic,Zoran} 23. Rxe4 dxe4 24. Bxe4 exd4) 23. Bxe4 {Prié, Eric: '?!' '?!'} (23. Rxe4 {(Prié, Eric) ChessCalisthenics: ''} dxe4 24. Bxe4 {ChessCalisthenics: ''} Rag8) 23... dxe4 24. Nf4 {Prié, Eric: '?' '?' Prié, Eric: 'It seems that White systematically makes it as easy as possible for his attacking opponent in this game, but he might have simply overlooked, in his far ahead calculation, that he was just getting mated after'} (24. Rxe4 {Prié, Eric} Qd5 25. Qf4 Nxg3 26. fxg3 f5 {ChessCalisthenics: '-+'} 27. Nf2 Kg6 (27... h1=Q+ 28. Rxh1 Rxh1 29. Kxh1 Kg6 30. c4 Qxc4 31. Re1) 28. c4 Qxc4 29. Re3 (29. Rf1 Qd5 30. Kh1 Raf8 31. Qf3 fxe4 32. Qg4+ Kh6 33. Qh3+ Qh5 34. Qxe6+ Kg7) 29... Nxd4 (29... Qd5+ 30. Qf3 Qxf3+ 31. Rxf3 Nxd4) 30. g4 Qd5+ 31. Kg3 Rac8 32. Re5 (32. gxf5+ Nxf5+) 32... Rc2 33. Rxd5 Ne2+ 34. Kf3 Nxf4 35. gxf5+ exf5 36. Rd4 Nh3) 24... e5 $1 25. Ne2 (25. Rxe4 {Prié, Eric} exf4 26. Qxf4 $19) 25... Nh4+ {Prié, Eric: '!' '!'} 26. Bxh4 Qg4+ {Prié, Eric: 'Petronijevic,Zoran: 'Black made advantage of White's passive play in the opening.'' Prié, Eric: 'Petronijevic,Zoran: 'Schwarz nutzte aus, dass Weiß in der Eröffnung sehr passiv spielte.''} 27. Ng3 {Prié, Eric} Qf3+ 28. Kxh2 (28. Kf1 h1=Q+ 29. Nxh1 Qxh1+ 30. Ke2 Qf3+ 31. Kf1 Rxh4 32. Qg5 fxg5 33. Rxe4 Rh1#) 28... Rxh4+ 29. Kg1 Rah8 30. Qh6 R8xh6 31. Rad1 (31. Rxe4 Rh1+ $1 32. Nxh1 Rxh1#) 31... Rh1+ 32. Nxh1 Rxh1# {0-1 (32) Spielmann,R-Nimzowitsch,A Karlstad 1923 [ChessCalisthenics] Prié, Eric: '0-1 (32) Spielmann,R-Nimzowitsch Aaron Karlstad 1923 [ChessCalisthenics]'} 0-1


