1. d4 {s.a. Tscharuschin: 226 KP, 217.  Müller: Veldes 1931, 78.  Varnusz: Aljechin, der Größte <1931/31>    Skinner/Verhoeven: Alexander Alekhine's Chess Games, 1427.   L'Echiquier 1931, S. 1386.} d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. Nc3 e6 5. Bg5 {Offering a promising -sacrifice. It is quite natural that Al.. liking this variation himself as White, avoids it and chooses the Cambridge Springs Defence, which he knows to a nicety.} Nbd7 (5... dxc4 6. e4 b5 7. e5 h6) 6. cxd5 {White, in his turn, avoids the complications of the Cambridge Springs, as earlier he avoided the dangers of the Meran variation.} exd5 7. e3 Be7 8. Bd3 O-O 9. Qc2 Re8 10. O-O (10. O-O-O {Müller setzt ein "!" mit Verweis auf die Partie Flohr-Asztalos im selben Turnier.} Qa5 { -b5/-b6/-c4. But Spielmann plays this game very carefully.}) 10... Nf8 11. h3 Nh5 12. Bxe7 Qxe7 13. Bf5 {Strives for simplification.} Bxf5 14. Qxf5 g6 15. Qd3 Nd7 16. Rfc1 f5 17. g3 Rf8 18. Na4 Qd6 { -g3:} 19. Qa3 $1 {The damaged 's are of no significance, in view of the fact that White obtaines lines for his 's.} Qxa3 (19... Qc7 $6 20. Kg2 {and White would go over to the attack himself by means of b4 or c5.}) 20. bxa3 Nhf6 21. Rab1 Rab8 22. Nc5 Nxc5 23. Rxc5 1/2-1/2


