1. e4 Nc6 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 d5 4. e5 b6 5. c3 Nce7 6. Bd3 a5 7. Qe2 Nf5 8. h4 h5 9. Ng5 g6 {The wrong overprotection move.} ({Correct was} 9... Nge7 {[%cal Yb1d2,Yd2f1,Yf2f3,Yg2g4] at once. Then White could not have executed the maneuver Nd2-f1 with f3 and g4, e.g.} 10. Nd2 c5 {and the base of the chain at d4 is shaky.}) 10. Nd2 Nge7 (10... Be7 {[%cal Yf2f3,Yg2g4] would have been better, for the overprotection has now no object, as White's f3 and g4 can no longer be prevented}) 11. Nf1 c5 12. f3 c4 13. Bc2 b5 14. g4 Ng7 {and White had the better position, although he lost in the end by an over-hasty attack. It can be seen that, in this game also, overprotection, if correctly carried out, would have been beneficial.} *


