{JvR: 'Euwe played a training match against Spielmann as preparation for a longer battle versus Flohr.'} 1. d4 {JvR DSB 1932, S.309 [Brinckmann]} d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. Nc3 e6 5. e3 Nbd7 6. Ne5 {JvR: '!?' JvR: 'Rubinstein was successful with this move.'} Be7 (6... Nxe5 {JvR} 7. dxe5 Nd7 8. f4 Bb4 {is even stronger.}) 7. Bd3 O-O 8. f4 c5 ({Euwe suggests} 8... dxc4 {JvR} 9. Bxc4) 9. cxd5 Nxd5 10. Nxd5 exd5 11. O-O Nf6 12. Bd2 cxd4 13. exd4 Ne4 14. Be3 Qb6 15. f5 {JvR: '?' JvR: 'Spielmann likes a sacrifice too much.'} ({In the witty variation} 15. Qe2 {JvR} f6 16. Nc4 Qc6 17. Nd2 f5 18. Nf3 {the knight returns to e5.}) 15... Qxb2 16. Qf3 Bg5 {JvR: '!' JvR: 'The attack is stopped immediately.'} 17. Bxe4 ({Euwe analyses} 17. Rfb1 {JvR} Nd2) (17. Rab1 {JvR} Bxe3+ 18. Qxe3 Qd2) 17... dxe4 18. Qg3 ({The point is} 18. Qxe4 {JvR} Bxf5 $1) 18... Bxe3+ 19. Qxe3 Bxf5 20. Rfb1 Qc2 21. Rxb7 Rab8 {JvR: '!'} 22. Rc1 ({Spielmann avoids} 22. Rxa7 {JvR} Rb2) 22... Qxa2 23. Rxb8 Rxb8 24. Nc6 Re8 25. h3 h6 26. Rc5 Qb1+ 27. Kf2 Bd7 28. d5 f5 29. Rc1 Qa2+ 30. Kg1 Qxd5 {JvR: 'Euwe countered strongly.'} 0-1


