1. e4 {JvR JvR 1)Aljechin: New York 1927.} e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. Bg5 Be7 5. exd5 {JvR: 'An old-fashioned exchange variation.'} (5. e5 {%02$14/=} Nfd7 6. Bxe7 Qxe7 7. f4 a6 8. Nf3 b5 9. Bd3 c5 10. dxc5 Nxc5 11. O-O Nc6 12. a3 g6 13. b4 Qa7 14. Kh1 Nxd3 15. cxd3 {...1/2-1/2, Mueller K.(2533) - Jussupow A.(2636), Altenkirchen 1999 Ch Germany}) 5... Nxd5 6. Bxe7 Qxe7 7. Qd2 (7. Nxd5 exd5+ 8. Qe2 Qxe2+ 9. Nxe2 Bf5 10. O-O-O O-O 11. Ng3 Bd7 12. Be2 Nc6 13. Bf3 Ne7 14. Rhe1 Rfe8 15. Nf1 {½-½ Hickl,J-Soffer,R/Bern zt 1990}) 7... Qb4 {JvR: '?!' '?!'} (7... O-O 8. O-O-O Qb4 {Alekhine}) 8. Nxd5 {JvR: 'Further exchange gives White an edge.'} Qxd2+ 9. Kxd2 exd5 10. Re1+ Be6 $6 {JvR: '?' '?'} (10... Kf8 {JvR: '!' '!' JvR: 'and a quick draw in Schlechter-Spielmann, San Sebastian 1911.'} 11. Bd3 Nc6 $11 {Keres}) 11. Nh3 {[%cal Yh3f4] JvR: '!' '!'} Nc6 {JvR: '?!' '?!'} (11... O-O 12. Nf4 Nc6 13. c3 a6 14. Be2 {[%cal Ye2f3] Lf3 Alekhine}) (11... c6 {!?} 12. Nf4 Ke7 {[%cal Yb8d7] Sd7= Kotov 'with the idea' Nd7}) 12. Bb5 Kd7 13. Nf4 Rae8 14. c4 $1 {!} Kd6 $8 15. c5+ Kd7 16. Re5 (16. Re3 $5 a6 $2 (16... f6 $5 17. Bxc6+ bxc6 18. Ra3 Rb8 19. Nxe6 Kxe6 20. Re1+ $16 {Alekhine}) 17. Bxc6+ Kxc6 18. Rhe1 Bd7 $2 (18... Kd7 19. Nh5 Rhg8 20. Rg3 $16) 19. Rxe8 (19. Nd3 $145 $1 $18) 19... Rxe8 20. Nh5 $18 {Euwe} Rxe1 $145 21. Kxe1 g6 22. Nf6 Bf5 $14) 16... f6 17. Rxe6 Rxe6 18. Nxe6 Kxe6 19. Bxc6 bxc6 {JvR: 'Black has a weakness.'} 20. Re1+ $14 {[%mdl 4096]  <-> } Kd7 (20... Kf7 {?!} 21. Kc3 $1 {!} Rb8 22. Re3 {''} Z0 23. a3 $140 $1 Z0 24. Kc2 Z0 25. Rb3 $18 {Alekhine}) 21. Kc3 Rb8 22. Re3 Rf8 23. Rg3 $1 Rf7 24. Kb4 (24. Rh3 $142 {Alekhine}) 24... Re7 25. Kc3 (25. Ka5 Re2 $1 26. Rxg7+ Kc8 $13 {Alekhine}) 25... Rf7 26. Rh3 $142 {Alekhine} h6 27. Kd2 $1 {[%cal Rh3a3] Ta3+- !} Re7 {JvR: 'Black defends his pawns.'} (27... Rf8 28. Ra3 Rb8 (28... Ra8 29. Ra6 {Alekhine}) 29. Kc3 Rb7 30. Ra6 $18 {Euwe}) (27... Kc8 $2 28. Ra3 Kb7 29. Re3 $18 {Kotov}) 28. Ra3 $2 (28. Re3 $5 {JvR: '!' '!'} Rxe3 (28... Rf7 $2 29. Ra3 $18) 29. Kxe3 Ke6 30. Kf4 g6 (30... g5+ {?} 31. Kg4) 31. g4 g5+ {JvR: 'The king's side is closed.'} 32. Ke3 Kd7 (32... f5 33. f3) 33. Kd3 Kc8 34. Kc3 Kb7 35. Kb4 Ka6 36. Ka4 Kb7 37. Ka5 a6 38. a4 Ka7 39. b3 $1 {!} Kb7 40. b4 Ka7 41. b5 axb5 42. axb5 Kb7 $1 {JvR: 'Alekhine missed in his calculations'} 43. b6 $1 {!} cxb6+ 44. cxb6 Kb8 45. Ka6 $1 {!} c5 46. dxc5 d4 47. b7 (47. c6 {JvR} d3 48. b7 d2) 47... d3 48. Kb6 d2 49. c6 d1=Q 50. c7# {Alekhine}) 28... Re4 {JvR: '!' '!'} 29. Ra4 Kc8 30. f3 Rh4 31. h3 Kb7 32. Ke3 f5 $1 {!} 33. Rb4+ Kc8 34. a4 {JvR: '?!' '?!' JvR: 'The pawn ending will be drawn after this move.'} g5 $2 {JvR: '?!' '?!'} (34... f4+ {JvR: '!' '!'} 35. Kf2 Rh5 {=} 36. Rb3 Rf5 37. Rd3 Rf7 38. Rd2 Re7 39. Re2 Rxe2+ 40. Kxe2 a5 $1 $11 {Alekhine JvR: '=' '='}) 35. a5 g4 (35... a6 $1 {JvR} 36. Kf2 {'+-' ! 'with the idea' Kg3-h2, g3} Rh5 37. Kg3 Rh4 38. Kh2 Rf4 39. b3 Kd7 $1 {escapes, because the sacrifice of the d-pawn is too risky.}) 36. hxg4 fxg4 37. a6 {!} gxf3 (37... g3 $2 {?} 38. f4 $1 $18 {Kotov}) 38. gxf3 Rh1 39. Rb7 Re1+ (39... Ra1 40. Rxa7 Kb8 41. Rb7+ Kc8 {JvR: 'was Spielmann's intention. He notices'} 42. Rb3 {JvR: '!' '!'} Rxa6 43. Ra3 {JvR: '+-' '+-'} Kb7 44. f4 $1 $18 {Alekhine}) 40. Kf4 $1 {!} (40. Kd2 $2 {?!} Re7 {!} 41. Rxa7 Kb8 42. Rb7+ Ka8 $11 {Alekhine !}) 40... Rd1 41. Ke5 Re1+ 42. Kf5 Rd1 43. Rxa7 $1 {!} Rxd4 44. Ra8+ Kd7 45. f4 Ra4 46. a7 $1 {!} h5 (46... d4 47. Ke4 h5 48. b3 Ra1 49. f5 Ke7 50. Kxd4 h4 51. Ke5 $18 {Alekhine}) 47. b3 $1 $18 {JvR: '!' '!' JvR: 'A subtle manoeuvre wins.'} (47. Ke5 Re4+ {Euwe}) 47... Ra1 48. Ke5 Re1+ 49. Kf6 Ra1 50. Ke5 Re1+ 51. Kd4 $1 {!} Rd1+ 52. Kc3 Ra1 53. f5 {!} Ke7 $8 54. Kd4 h4 55. Ke5 Re1+ 56. Kf4 Ra1 57. Kg5 Rg1+ (57... h3 58. Rh8 {!} Rxa7 59. Rxh3 {'+-'} Ra1 60. f6+ {JvR: '!' '!'} Kf7 61. Rh7+ Kf8 62. Rxc7 $18 {Alekhine}) 58. Kxh4 Ra1 59. Kg5 Rg1+ 60. Kf4 Ra1 61. Ke5 Re1+ 62. Kd4 Ra1 63. Kc3 Ra3 64. Kb2 Ra6 65. b4 Kf7 66. Kb3 Ra1 67. f6 $1 Ra6 68. b5 cxb5 69. Kb4 {JvR: 'Alekhine ended at the second place.'} (69. Kb4 c6 70. Rh8) 1-0


