1. e4 {Max Adolf Albin was born in Bucarest on 18 January 1870 and died in Vienna 1920. Max Adolf Albin travelled through Danmark and Sweden in 1913 on a simultaneous tour. It appears that he arrived based on an invitation to his late father, Adolf Albin (*1848, +1913).  Albin visited several cities and played a number of simuls and five match games against Gustaf Nyholm.} e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. Bc4 Bc5 5. d3 d6 6. h3 Be6 7. Bg5 h6 8. Bxf6 Qxf6 9. Nd5 Bxd5 10. Bxd5 Ne7 11. Bb3 g5 12. Qe2 O-O-O 13. O-O-O h5 14. Nd2 Ng6 15. g3 Qe7 16. Nf1 Rdf8 17. Ne3 Bxe3+ 18. Qxe3 Kb8 19. Rdf1 c6 20. c3 f5 21. exf5 Rxf5 22. Bd1 Qf7 23. Kb1 Ne7 24. c4 c5 25. g4 Rf4 26. a3 h4 27. Ba4 Rf8 28. Rh2 Qg6 29. Bc2 Qf6 30. f3 Nc6 31. Rhf2 Nd4 32. Bd1 a6 33. Qd2 Qg6 34. Ka2 Ne6 35. Be2 Rd4 36. b4 Nf4 37. bxc5 dxc5 38. Qe3 Qd6 39. Rh2 Rd8 40. Re1 e4 41. fxe4 Nxd3 42. e5 Qe6 43. Bxd3 Rxd3 44. Qc1 R8d4 45. Rc2 Rxh3 46. Kb1 Rb3+ 47. Ka1 Rxg4 48. Re3 Rg3 49. Rxb3 Rxb3 50. Qxg5 Rxa3+ 51. Kb2 Qh3 52. Kc1 Qf1+ 0-1


