1. c4 c6 2. e4 d5 3. exd5 cxd5 4. d4 {Caro-Kann: Panov-Botvinnik attack} Nf6 5. Nc3 Nc6 6. Bg5 Qb6 $6 (6... dxc4 {Was probably the better idea.} 7. d5 Na5 $14) 7. cxd5 {The start of White's trap.} Qxb2 {The poison will become obvious in a moment.} (7... Bg4 {Also leads to trouble.} 8. f3 Nxd4 9. fxg4 Qxb2 10. Rc1 $18 {2.50}) 8. Rc1 {Protecting the knight.} (8. dxc6 Qxc3+ 9. Bd2 Qxd4 $19) 8... Nb4 {Bringing the knight into play. However...} 9. Na4 {Attacking-trapping the Queen: the offered pawn not only is poison but force-fed!} Qxa2 (9... Qa3 10. Rc3 Qxa2 11. Bc4 Bg4 12. Nf3 Bxf3 13. gxf3 Nc2+ 14. Qxc2 Qa1+ 15. Qc1 Qxc1+ 16. Rxc1 $18 {Same story: White +2.50}) 10. Bc4 Bg4 11. Nf3 Bxf3 12. gxf3 {Black resigned here.} Nc2+ {The trapped Queen must sac her knight.} 13. Qxc2 Qxc2 14. Rxc2 {With White ahead by almost 2.50} 1-0


