1. d4 {With three round to go Spielmann led Nimzowitsch by ½ point, so Nimzowitsch was obliged to exert himself to the utmost to gain the full point. Their clash almost certainly decided the destination of the first prize.} d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 $6 4. Nc3 dxc4 5. a4 $5 Bf5 6. Ne5 e6 7. f3 Nbd7 (7... c5 8. dxc5 Qxd1+ 9. Kxd1 Bxc5 10. e4 Bg6 11. Bxc4 Nc6 12. Nxc6 bxc6 13. Bf4 Nh5 14. Bd2 Rb8 15. Kc2 e5 16. Rhe1 Nf4 17. Bxf4 exf4 18. Rad1 Ke7 19. Ne2 Bf2 20. Nd4 Rbc8 21. Rf1 Bxd4 22. Rxd4 Rhd8 23. Rfd1 Rxd4 24. Rxd4 f6 25. Kc3 Be8 26. b3 Rc7 27. Bg8 h5 28. Kc4 h4 29. h3 Rd7 30. Rxd7+ Kxd7 31. Kc5 g5 32. Bc4 Kc7 33. Be6 Bh5 34. b4 Bg6 35. Bc4 Be8 {Nimzowitsch's victory in this game was all the more praiseworthy in that Spielmann was then at the height of his powers. In the next round the Austrian GM defeated Capablanca thus assuring himself of a share in second prize.} 36. Be6 Bg6 37. a5 { Re8}) 8. e4 Bg6 9. Nxc4 $1 Nb6 10. Ne5 (10. Be3) 10... Nfd7 (10... Nbd7) 11. Nxg6 $1 hxg6 12. a5 Nc8 13. d5 exd5 14. exd5 Nf6 15. a6 bxa6 16. Qa4 Qc7 (16... Nb6 17. Qxc6+ (17. Qxa6 Nfxd5) 17... Nfd7 18. d6) (16... Rb8) 17. Bxa6 Bc5 18. Qxc6+ Qxc6 $2 19. dxc6 Ne7 20. Bb7 Rd8 21. c7 Rd6 22. c8=Q+ Nxc8 23. Bxc8 O-O 24. Bb7 Re8+ 25. Kf1 Re7 26. Ba8 Rd4 $6 27. Bg5 Re8 28. Bc6 Re6 29. Ba4 $1 { 30.Rf2} Nh7 30. h4 Nxg5 31. hxg5 Rd2 32. Ne4 Rxb2 33. Nxc5 { h4, Rff5, Rc5, Rg6} Ree2 34. Ne4 $1 Kf8 35. Re1 Rxe1+ 36. Kxe1 Rb1+ 37. Bd1 1-0


